 Covariances for 24-Mg in the resonance region were estimated     1225 1451
 using the kernel approach, which covers the range of the         1225 1451
 resonance region up to 520 keV. In this region, Mughabghab       1225 1451
 values given in Atlas were used. Differences between absolute    1225 1451
 values of data in Atlas of Neutron Resonances and ENDF/B-VII.0   1225 1451
 have been taken into account, leading to enhanced cross section  1225 1451
 uncertainties.                                                   1225 1451
                                                                  1225 1451
 Covariances at higher energies were treated as the fast          1225 1451
 neutron range. These fast neutron covariances were obtained at   1225 1451
 BNL using EMPIRE calculated sensitivities and KALMAN code to     1225 1451
 incorporate experimental data. Both elemental and isotopic data  1225 1451
 are available for total cross sections on 24-Mg. Some of them,   1225 1451
 below about 7 MeV, had to be filtered out, or the matrix would   1225 1451
 be too large for the KALMAN filter. Above 8 MeV, uncertainties   1225 1451
 come from the EMPIRE/KALMAN approach. In between these energies  1225 1451
 the uncertainties are based on the Bonner experimental           1225 1451
 uncertainty. For inelastic and capture there are only sparse and 1225 1451
 inconsistent data so the covariance estimates are essentially    1225 1451
 model-based.                                                     1225 1451
